---
import Page from '../layouts/Page.astro';
import { withBase } from '../utils/paths';
---
<Page
  title="About"
  heroTitle="About Stillwater"
  heroSubtitle="A non-sectarian centre for meditation and contemplative practice in the heart of the Hudson Valley."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="about-layout">

        <div class="prose">
          <h2>Our Mission</h2>
          <p>
            Stillwater Dharma Center exists to make genuine contemplative practice
            accessible to everyone. We offer teachings and courses rooted in the Buddhist
            tradition — particularly in meditation and compassion training — in a form that
            is clear, practical, and relevant to contemporary life.
          </p>
          <p>
            We believe that the ability to find stillness within the mind, and to develop
            genuine warmth toward ourselves and others, is not a luxury but a necessity —
            and that these capacities can be cultivated through training.
          </p>

          <h2>Our Approach: Rimé</h2>
          <p>
            Rimé — the Tibetan word for "non-sectarian" — is not a new tradition but a
            spirit of open inquiry and respect for multiple lineages of wisdom. At
            Stillwater we draw from Tibetan Buddhist traditions (Kagyu, Nyingma, Gelug),
            Zen, and Theravada, offering what is most helpful without insisting that any
            one path is the only way.
          </p>
          <p>
            You do not need to be a Buddhist, or hold any particular belief, to practise
            with us. The techniques we teach are universal. What matters is the sincerity
            of your intention to look inward and to cultivate kindness.
          </p>

          <h2>Meditation &amp; Wellbeing</h2>
          <p>
            Research over the past three decades has confirmed what practitioners have
            known for centuries: meditation and compassion training genuinely help.
            Studies show significant reductions in stress, anxiety, and depression;
            improvements in focus, emotional regulation, and sleep; and measurable
            increases in wellbeing and prosocial behaviour.
          </p>
          <p>
            Our courses are informed by this research and are taught in a way that
            meets people where they are — whether they come seeking relief from stress,
            greater clarity, deeper meaning, or simply a community of like-minded people.
          </p>

          <h2>Our Space</h2>
          <p>
            Our centre sits on a quiet property on the edge of Woodstock, surrounded by
            mature trees and the sounds of the forest. The main meditation hall seats up
            to thirty practitioners and is equipped with cushions, benches, and chairs.
            The space is simple, warm, and conducive to practice.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are accessible by car from across the Hudson Valley and from New York City.
            See our <a href={withBase('/contact/')}>contact and directions page</a> for details.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="about-sidebar">
          <div class="infobox">
            <p class="infobox-title">Centre Information</p>
            <dl>
              <dt>Founded</dt>      <dd>2019</dd>
              <dt>Location</dt>    <dd>Woodstock, NY</dd>
              <dt>Tradition</dt>   <dd>Rimé (non-sectarian)</dd>
              <dt>Language</dt>    <dd>English</dd>
              <dt>Access</dt>      <dd>Ground floor, wheelchair accessible</dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
          <div class="infobox" style="margin-top:1.5rem">
            <p class="infobox-title">Weekly Schedule</p>
            <dl>
              <dt>Thursday</dt> <dd>Drop-in sitting 6–7:30pm</dd>
              <dt>Courses</dt>  <dd>See programmes page</dd>
              <dt>Retreats</dt> <dd>Quarterly</dd>
            </dl>
          </div>
          <div style="margin-top:1.5rem">
            <a href={withBase('/programs/')} class="btn btn--primary" style="width:100%;justify-content:center">
              View all programs
            </a>
          </div>
        </aside>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>

<style>
  .about-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 300px;
    gap: 4rem;
    align-items: start;
  }
  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-layout { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .about-sidebar { order: -1; }
  }
</style>
